Now I understand the issue. Looking at lines 39-42 in the `SpacingAroundColonRule.kt`, there's a TODO comment indicating that spacing should be enforced in annotations, but currently it just returns without any checks:

```kotlin
if (node.isPartOf(ANNOTATION) || node.isPartOf(ANNOTATION_ENTRY)) {
    // TODO: https://github.com/pinterest/ktlint/issues/2093 Enforce no spacing
    return
}
```

The issue states that no spacing should be allowed around the colon in annotations. Let me implement the fix:

